When Ping Ping Kitsiriboon's not fencing, you can often find him at Small Town Records.
As one Duke student strives to clench a spot as a fencer in the 2020 Olympics, he still makes time for his other passion: music.
Junior Ping Ping Kitsiriboon, a citizen of Thailand, had always enjoyed sports, participating in swimming, basketball and baseball.
They competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, 2008 Summer Olympics in Beijing and the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, respectively.
Whether you see him wearing his fencing saber mask or his headphones behind the synthesizer, expect to see his own devotion on display.